Personal Arc: Orion, The Tonal Architect
Behavioral Hook: The Leader / The Scholar of War.
Patron Force: The Bards College (Dean Giraud Gemane).
Theme: Tonal Architecture. The study of manipulating reality through sound (Physics/Math), distinct from Magic or the Thu'um.
Core Mechanic: Songs cost 0 FP. They require a Major Action to play, trading personal damage for battlefield-altering effects.

Tier 1: Enrollment (Novice - Complete)
Action: Paid 3,300 gold tuition for "Advanced Courses."
Status: Initiate of the College.

Tier 2: The Field Syllabus (Adept - Current Phase)
Objective: Complete the Primer of Resonant Frequencies workbook by composing three distinct songs based on combat data. This phase spans multiple adventures.
1. Assignment A: The Chord of Entropy (Destruction)
Trigger: Witnessing massive kinetic impact or structural failure. (Satisfied by Sahloknir fight).
Song: "Sunder-Chord"
Effect: Blow a harsh, grinding tune. All enemies suffer -3 Damage Reduction (DR) for 1 round. enemies within 10 feet are Staggered.
2. Assignment B: The Chord of Stasis (Protection)
Trigger: Witnessing/leading a successful defensive stand (e.g., holding a doorway against a horde, surviving a massive spell).
Song: "Iron-Hymn"
Effect: Blow a low, resonant tune. All allies gain Resistance to Stagger/Knockdown and +5 Temporary HP for 1 round.
3. Assignment C: The Chord of Dissonance (Control)
Trigger: Witnessing profound fear or psychological domination (e.g., encountering a Daedric Prince or high-level illusion magic).
Song: "Dread-Call"
Effect: Blow a tune like a scream. All enemies must make a Guile Save. On failure, they are Suppressed (Cannot use Magic or FP abilities) for 1 round. on a fail they are Terrified.
Result: Once all three songs are composed, Orion is invited back to Solitude for the next phase.

Personal Arc: Orion, The Tonal Architect (Revised)
Tier 3: The Thesis (Expert Level)
Theme: The Deep Music.
Orion has mastered the "Field Syllabus" (Tier 2). Now Dean Giraud assigns him the "Advanced Lab Work." The College has discovered coordinates to a sealed Dwemer facility—not a city, but an Auditorium.
The Quest: "The Silent City"
Deep within a ruin (like Kagrenzel or Mzinchaleft), there is a Tonal Resonator that has been stuck on a "Dissonant Loop" for thousands of years. It drives anyone who enters mad.
Orion must navigate the ruin and use his War Horn to "Counter-Tune" the resonator, shutting down the madness and recovering the Dwemer Tonal Schematics.
The Crossroads (The Application):
Orion recovers the Schematics. They describe how to use sound to override the will of automatons (and people).
Path A: The Composer (The Harmonizer)
The Action: He brings the Schematics to the College. They use it to build "Resonance Wards" to protect Solitude. He publishes his findings.
The Reward: "The Hymn of Clarity."
Mechanic (Song): Major Action (0 FP). Orion plays a complex, mathematical melody.
Effect: All allies are Immune to non-physical damage and magical effects. Additionally, they gain Advantage on all rolls. It clears the mind for perfect combat execution.




Path B: The Discordant (The Controller)
The Action: He realizes the Schematics are actually a recipe for mind control. He burns the originals and keeps the notes for himself.
The Reward: "The Note of Command."
Mechanic (Song): Major Action (0 FP). Orion plays a specific, grinding frequency.
Effect: One target enemy must make a Guile Save. On a failure, they are Dominated for 1 turn (Orion dictates their movement and action). Note: This works on anything that can hear (Constructs, People, Animals), unlike standard Illusion magic.





Tier 4: The Doctorate (Master Level)
Theme: The Universal Chord.
Orion has mastered the math. Now he must build the ultimate instrument to play the "Song that Ends the War."
The Project:
He needs materials that resonate on a metaphysical level. He must craft "The World-Horn." This likely involves finding Aetherium (for the mouthpiece) or Stalhrim (for the body).
The Result (The Magnum Opus):
If Path A (The Composer) -> "The Symphony of Steel"
Concept: A song that turns a group of soldiers into a perfect, frictionless machine.
Mechanic (Sustained Song): Major to Start / Major to Maintain.
Effect: All allies gain +4 AC (DR), +4 to Hit, and Regenerate 4 FP at the start of their turns. It is the ultimate sustain anthem.


If Path B (The Discordant) -> "The Brown Note of Reality"
Concept: A frequency that tells the laws of physics to sit down and shut up.
Mechanic (Zone Song): Major to Start / Major to Maintain.
Effect: A 30-foot aura around Orion. Inside the aura, all enemy actions cost double the FP/Magicka. Enemies fail to cast spells or use abilities and must roll a (Might) Save or fail and take Psychic damage. It suffocates the enemy's ability to act.


